# Git merge driver configuration for conflict-prone files
#
# Setup (run once per machine):
#   git config --global merge.ours.driver true
#
# After running the above, git will use 'true' (exit 0) as the merge driver.
# A successful exit with no output means git keeps the "ours" version unchanged,
# which is the desired behavior for lockfiles and bot-managed files.
#
# If you hit a lockfile conflict after a rebase/merge:
#   1. Abort the conflicted merge: git merge --abort
#   2. Re-merge: git merge origin/main
#      OR for a rebase: git rebase origin/main
#   3. Then regenerate: npm install  (for package-lock.json)
#
# Key convention: Never hand-merge lockfiles. Always regenerate.

# Prevent merge conflicts in lockfiles — keep ours (delete and regenerate instead)
package-lock.json merge=ours linguist-generated=true

# Bot-managed on main; feature branches must not touch them
CHANGELOG.md merge=ours
.release-please-manifest.json merge=ours

# Route/barrel files: prefer append-only registration to reduce parallel-feature conflicts
# When two PRs conflict in App.tsx or similar, prefer a human/agent to resolve